name: Gyukatsu Motomura Harajuku
locationString: Shibuya, Tokyo, Tokyo Prefecture, Kanto
description: Very popular "Gyukatsu" (beef cutlet) restaurant that now runs 6 branches in Tokyo (as of October 2016). Note that Shibuya branches are always very crowded and you should expect to wait for an hour or so, I'd suggest you get there 30-60 minutes prior or go to the other branches (less crowded). The beef cutlet is deep-fried outside very quickly, so it's fairly rare inside. It used to be more cooked and you were to eat it as is, but as they became popular among visitors from overseas, they started serving a stone grill along with the cutlet so that you can cook as you like. I imagine there was an increasing feedback from the customers that the meat was too rare. I actually liked more the way it used to be, but guess it's better now for non-Japanese customers. It's 1,300 JPY (130g of beef) and comes as a combo and the photo abve is 2,100 JPY combo (260g of beef). I'd say 130g would be enough for most people.

description: 日本と台湾の文化を融合した、カオスを楽しむ肉汁水餃子専門店餃包。東京都港区・六本木交差点近くの大通り沿い、交番の隣の路面店です。気軽に楽しめる中華・屋台風の餃子酒場（居酒屋）です。満席、行列になることが多く、相席をお願いする場合があります。世界中のお客様との一期一会の出会いと交流の場として楽しみください。 お食事は、小籠包のような肉汁と国産豚100%の餃子餡をもっちりした皮で包んだ餃包が看板商品です。ぜひお試しください。点心や新商品の火鍋餃包、人気のよだれ鶏、豚の角煮、都内で一番美味しいプレミアムモルツ生ビール（サントリー樽生の超達人認定店舗）、季節のサワーなどが飲めます。ルーレットを回して遊ぶ運試しハイボールでワイワイするのもおすすめの楽しみ方です。お酒を自分で作ると安くなるマイセルフ制度や飲み放題もオススメ。80歳を超えたスタッフのウクレレライブがあったりします。 19時〜22時は満席でお並びいただく事が多いため、お早めにご来店されることをおすすめします。

name: Ise Sueyoshi
locationString: Nishiazabu, Minato, Tokyo, Tokyo Prefecture, Kanto
description: Ise Sueyoshi is a private Japanese restaurant in Tokyo. Placed between Roppongi and Hiroo. We serving traditional "Kaiseki"style Japanese cuisine with English guide. The owner trained in "Kikunoi" restaurant. After trained,spend a year in Tronto,Canada and trained around the world. Returning to Japan with a desire to 'disseminate Japanese cuisine as a part of this country's culture', he headed back to his native Mie to form connections with farmers and other producers. Blessed with the ample fruits of both the mountains and the sea, the prefecture has long been known as a treasure trove of foodstuffs. He finally opened his own place in 2015, focusing on ingredients from the ancient city of Ise. Kappo Ise Sueyoshi in the heart of Tokyo is ideal for enjoying the four seasons of Japan.
